•  is the  of every Rust program. It’s where the program begins running.• Rust  for a function named  when you run a program.• That’s why it must be called  — .• it is required in executable programsBut what is the parenthesis  after  for ?• These are .fn main() {
    // your code here
}
This function takes  (no parameters)You can't define main with an input or parameter 
I.efn main(input: &str) {
